::Spears::

She went to the outside of the ship to think.  She walked around the 
outside of the ship and kept glancing at the scortched hull.  She 
could see into a few of the room inside the ship through some of the 
holes.  She paced back and forth, thinking about what thier next move 
might be.  She knew an attack on the Preds would possably by them 
time. But the Preds were gaining in numbers and they were getting 
stronger.  She needed to find a way to even the odds.  What could 
make the scales even, she thought. She paced and kept pacing, deep in 
thought and worry.
